GPSR: Updated General Product Safety Regulations

As of 13th December 2024, new regulations have been introduced to enhance product safety for consumers and provide clearer guidelines for businesses shipping to the EU and NI. The question on most peoples mind is Does GPSR Apply to Me?

The key change for UK-based businesses and online sellers is the requirement to appoint a ‘responsible person’ based in the EU or NI. This individual is responsible for overseeing compliance and product safety requirements. Additionally, all packaging must adhere to GPSR labelling regulations.

Frequently Asked Questions

What is the cheapest international shipping?

Our most affordable international shipping service starts from just £6.56 with Parcel2Go. Get a quote to compare our cheapest parcel delivery.

Parcel2Go’s Lowest Price Guarantee means no matter what you’re sending, or where you’re shipping to, using Parcel2Go will always be the cheapest way to ship internationally! And if you find a cheaper price elsewhere, we’ll refund you the difference.

How to ship internationally from the UK?

Sending a parcel abroad is easy with Parcel2Go:

  1. Get a quote and choose the drop off or collection service that best suits your needs

  2. Book your parcel and we’ll send you all the customs documentation you need for your parcel to get from A to B with no delays

  3. Package your parcel and take it to your chosen drop off point or have it collected directly from your home

It’s that easy! And if you have questions about customs duty or VAT, use our International Shipping Hub to help you. Or contact Parcel2Go’s customer service team, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.

Who pays for international shipping?

There are several ways you can pay for the import fees involved with international shipping, but if you don’t want the person receiving your parcel to have to pay a penny, choose a service that offers Delivery Duties Paid (DDP).

Look out for a banner that says ‘Pre-Pay Delivery Duty Available’ in our booking process and choose one of these services to pay for all international delivery duties up front.

Other ways you can pay for delivery duties are through Delivery Duties Unpaid (DDU) or if you’re a business shipper, you can use Import-One-Stop-Shop (IOSS).

How long does international shipping take?

With a variety of express delivery services for international postage, your parcel could arrive at its destination as soon as the next working day! For example, FedEx Express can get your parcel to the USA within just 1 day.

Whether you’re sending a parcel to Germany or shipping to the USA, you can choose between next day delivery, economy and super economy courier services. Standard shipping is usually between 3-5 days, but will vary depending on your parcel’s destination.

Do I have to pay customs charges for international delivery?

You may have to pay customs and VAT but the amount will depend on the country you're shipping to as well as the value of your parcel and its contents. You can work out exactly how much customs duty and fees you’ll need to pay during the booking process. Get a quote to get started.

For more information, use our International Shipping Hub to find out more about sending gifts abroad and the EU VAT rates for each country.

Will my international postage have tracking?

All parcels booked through Parcel2Go are fully trackable, from the moment we receive your parcel up until it arrives as its final destination. Already booked? Track a parcel here.
